The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Srinivasan walks out
                                                                                                                       7                                      Srinivasan walks out
                      
	Chennai: Annoyed by a question on the Indian Premier League (IPL) controversy thrown at him, the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) secretary and the Chennai Super Kings part owner, N Srinivasan, Friday walked out of a press conference, where he happily talked about his team winning the title this year.         
	Srinivasan, who announced before the conerence that he would not answer questions other than those on the IPL, talked about his side missing the inaugural edition title and this years Champions League Twenty20.         
	But when a reporter asked about his comments on the IPL controversy, he ended the conference immediately.         
	Before that, Srinivasan said he was delighted to have won the IPL III and also the Fair Play Trophy.         
	Meanwhile, suspended IPL commissioner Lalit Modi has agreed to hand over the documents related to franchise bids and media rights of the Twenty20 league which the BCCI had sought for.         
	N Srinivasan had written a letter to Modi asking to return the missing documents to BCCI CAO Ratnakar Shetty and Modi has agreed to do that, a television channel claimed. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
